---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is a bet?",
    answer:
      "A bet is anything you commit to building — a product, a tool, a game, a community project. It means you're putting your time and skills on the line for something you believe in. The outcome might be revenue, impact, or personal growth.",
  },
  {
    question: "Do I have to build 12 things in 12 months?",
    answer:
      "No. The name \"12 in 12\" is aspirational, not a requirement. You set your own pace. Some builders ship monthly, others take longer on a single bet. What matters is that you're building and sharing your journey.",
  },
  {
    question: "What are the three motivations?",
    answer:
      'Every bet has a motivation: <strong>For Profit</strong> (building a business), <strong>For Impact</strong> (solving a problem for a community), or <strong>For Craft</strong> (learning, experimenting, having fun). You pick one when you create a bet, and you can change it if your motivation evolves.',
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need coding or technical skills?",
    answer:
      'Not at all. Some builders use AI tools to vibe-code their projects, others are experienced developers, and some build non-technical products entirely. Use whatever tools work for you — including <a href="https://claude.ai" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">AI assistants</a>.',
  },
  {
    question: "What does it cost?",
    answer:
      "The platform is free. You can create a profile, place bets, share updates, and participate in the community feed at no cost. Paid cohorts with dedicated leads may be offered in the future.",
  },
  {
    question: "What if my bet doesn't work out?",
    answer:
      "That's part of the story. A parked or canceled bet with an honest reflection is more valuable to the community than a silent disappearance. The platform prompts you to share what happened and what you learned.",
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need to share my progress publicly?",
    answer:
      'Sharing is encouraged but not required. Public accountability helps most builders stay on track, and your journey might inspire others. You can share updates on your <a href="/profile" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">profile page</a> and in the community feed.',
  },
  {
    question: "Can I join anytime?",
    answer:
      'Yes — there are no cohort start dates or enrollment windows. <a href="/join" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">Join</a>, create your profile, and place your first bet whenever you\'re ready.',
  },
  {
    question: "How is this different from a project tracker?",
    answer:
      "Project trackers show status. 12in12 shows the story. When you change your bet's status, the platform prompts you to share the narrative — your thesis, your progress, your outcome. That story is what the community reads and learns from.",
  },
  {
    question: "Who is behind 12in12?",
    answer:
      'It\'s built by <a href="/dorelljames" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">Dorell James</a>, a builder who wanted a community to share the journey of shipping products. The platform itself is one of his bets.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="lg:text-center">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl"
      >
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-12">
      <dl
        class="space-y-10 md:space-y-0 md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-x-8 md:gap-y-12"
      >
        {
          faqs.map((faq) => (
            <div>
              <dt class="text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-gray-900">
                {faq.question}
              </dt>
              <dd class="mt-2 text-base text-gray-500" set:html={faq.answer} />
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
